    <h1>10 Fun facts about pets : </h1>
    <ul>
      <li>Dogs have a sense of smell that is 10,000 times more powerful than humans. They can even detect some diseases
        like cancer and diabetes.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>A group of pugs is called a "grumble" because of their snorting and grunting noises.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Cats can jump up to six times their body length in a single bound!
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Dogs can make over 100 different facial expressions, while cats have only about 20.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Many dog breeds were originally bred for specific purposes, such as hunting, herding, or guarding. However,
        now they make great companions for a wide variety of lifestyles.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Cats are natural hunters and have been known to bring their owners "presents" such as mice, birds, or even
        small snakes!
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>The oldest known cat was named Creme Puff, who lived to be 38 years and 3 days old.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Some dogs have webbed feet, which helps them swim better. These breeds include Labrador Retrievers, Portuguese
        Water Dogs, and Newfoundlands.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Cats are able to rotate their ears 180 degrees, which helps them to pinpoint the source of a sound.
      </li>
      <br>

      <li>Dogs have been known to dream and may even make noises or twitch their legs while sleeping.
      </li>
      <br>
    </ul>

